usage: lgit [--version] [--help] <command> [<args>]

These are common Lgit commands used in various situations:

start a working area (see also: lgit help tutorial)
   init       Create an empty Lgit repository or reinitialize an existing one

work on the current change (see also: lgit help everyday)
   add        Add file contents to the index
   rm         Remove files from the working tree and from the index

examine the history and state (see also: lgit help revisions)
   status     Show the working tree status

grow, mark and tweak your common history
   branch     List, create, or delete branches
   checkout   Switch branches or restore working tree files
   commit     Record changes to the repository
   merge      Join two or more development histories together

'lgit help -a' and 'lgit help -g' list available subcommands and some
concept guides. See 'git help <command>' or 'lgit help <concept>'
to read about a specific subcommand or concept.
